<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="73 - 96" title="Polychaete fauna of the Aegean Sea: inventory and new information" volume="66" year="2000">Arvanitidis (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
but specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nephtyidae" genus="Aglaophamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglaophamus malmgreni" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="malmgreni">Aglaophamus malmgreni</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="ThÃ©el">Theel</normalizedToken>
, 1897) by 
<bibRefCitation author="von Marenzeller, Emil" journalOrPublisher="Denkschriften der Akademie der Wissenschaften, Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="295 - 323" title="Berichte der Commission fuer Oceanographische Forschungen. Achte Reihe. Forschungen im oestlichen Mittelmeere. Zoologische Ergebnisse XIII. Polychaeten des Grundes, gesammelt 1893, 1894" volume="74" year="1902">von Marenzeller (1902)</bibRefCitation>
could belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nephtyidae" genus="Aglaophamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglaophamus pulcher" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pulcher">Aglaophamus pulcher</taxonomicName>
(see notes there). In the Mediterranean also known from abyssal canyons and plains in the western basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Ravara, Ascensao" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 68" title="Nephtyidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from southern Europe" volume="2682" year="2010">Ravara et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
), otherwise distributed in the North East Atlantic. May have been confused in the past with 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nephtyidae" genus="Nephtys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nephtys hystricis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hystricis">Nephtys hystricis</taxonomicName>
McIntosh, 1900 and 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nephtyidae" genus="Nephtys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nephtys incisa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="incisa">Nephtys incisa</taxonomicName>
Malmgren 1865 (
<bibRefCitation author="Rainer, Sebastian F" journalOrPublisher="Helgolaender Meeresuntersuchungen" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="65 - 96" title="The genus Nephtys (Polychaeta: Phyllodocida) of northern Europe: a review of species, including the description of N. pulchra sp. n. and a key to the Nephtyidae" volume="45" year="1991">Rainer 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and therefore been overlooked in the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
